Concourse Pipeline setup

1. Install visual studio code : https://code.visualstudio.com/
2. enable bash/linux/ubuntu terminal: by default VS code terminal will be powershell
    - open VS code
	- open terminal cntrl+`
	- open command palette cntrl+shift+p
	- type- select default profile
	- select ubuntu
	-click on + icon on terminal window
	- the new terminal will show ur ubuntu

3. Install fly for linux
	- download fly for linux https://<concourseURL>, botom left of page u can see version :6.7.6 and fly [icon for windows,mac and linux). Click on linux icon, fly cli will start auto downloading
	copy fly from downloads to  /mnt/c/concourse
	chmod +x fly
	run sudo install fly /usr/local/bin
	type fly --version to check
	<systemlocalpath>/mnt/c/concourse$ fly --version
	6.7.6
